<subSubSection box="[199,1259,1663,1688]" pageId="13" pageNumber="538" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,151,1941]" box="[199,1259,1663,1688]" pageId="13" pageNumber="538">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,326,1663,1688]" pageId="13" pageNumber="538">Etymology</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[340,568,1664,1687]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="538" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tigrinus">
<emphasis box="[340,568,1664,1687]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="538">Mesoconius tigrinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is named for the tiger–striped abdominal and thoracic pleura.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="538" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,151,1941]" pageId="13" pageNumber="538">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,1700,1725]" pageId="13" pageNumber="538">Comments</emphasis>
. Although 
<taxonomicName box="[474,711,1701,1724]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="538" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tigrinus">
<emphasis box="[474,711,1701,1724]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="538">Mesoconius tigrinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
superficially resembles the similarly yellow and black 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="538" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hemithorax">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="538">M. hemithorax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, these two species differ in many important details, the most obvious of which are the lack of postocellar bristles and the rounded katatergite in 
<taxonomicName box="[716,841,1773,1796]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="538" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tigrinus">
<emphasis box="[716,841,1773,1796]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="538">M. tigrinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(in contrast with the nipple-like katatergite and well developed postocellars in 
<taxonomicName box="[442,606,1808,1832]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="538" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hemithorax">
<emphasis box="[442,606,1808,1832]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="538">M. hemithorax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). The stout, short, tubular distal distiphallus of this species is most similar to the greatly reduced distal distiphallus of 
<emphasis box="[639,852,1844,1868]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="538">
<taxonomicName box="[639,847,1844,1868]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="538" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigrihumeralis">M. nigrihumeralis</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
Both 
<taxonomicName box="[921,1045,1845,1868]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="538" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tigrinus">
<emphasis box="[921,1045,1845,1868]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="538">M. tigrinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1101,1305,1844,1868]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="538" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigrihumeralis">
<emphasis box="[1101,1305,1844,1868]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="538">M. nigrihumeralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are outside the clade including all other Central American 
<taxonomicName box="[677,811,1880,1903]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="538" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[677,811,1880,1903]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="538">Mesoconius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,151,1941]" box="[199,1330,1916,1941]" pageId="13" pageNumber="538">
<taxonomicName box="[199,427,1917,1940]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="538" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tigrinus">
<emphasis box="[199,427,1917,1940]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="538">Mesoconius tigrinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a close mimic of the sympatric ichneumonid wasp 
<taxonomicName authority="Cresson." authorityName="Cresson." box="[1028,1330,1916,1940]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Exetastes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="538" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tarsalis">
<emphasis box="[1028,1225,1916,1940]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="538">Exetastes tarsalis</emphasis>
Cresson.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
